Defendant Cornell L Hutchison in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Nathaniel E Adamson for Denis Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Statements made as to sentencing.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS, with credit for 29 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR, same terms and conditions as probation to apply.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:  
*Serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction (IMPOSED AND STAYED); 
*Complete Dosage Probation Program; 
*AODA assessment and follow through with recommended programming; 
*Maintain absolute sobriety;
*No new offenses;
*Cooperate with agent;
*Complete and follow through with all programming and conditions deemed appropriate by agent;
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges. 
All costs and surcharges to be paid during the period of probation.  Any unpaid amount is ordered converted to a civil judgment.  If revoked, DOC shall collect up to 25% of prison funds.  Remaining balance to be paid during the period of extended supervision. Any unpaid amount is ordered converted to a civil judgment. 
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

